  "text": "... (3) where g is the maximum number of greylevels in the input image (e.g. 256), R is a given segment, R is the mean value of the grey-levels in , and = 1/6. Moreover, parameter determines the amount of roughness and smoothness of segmentation. With higher values of , more segments are produced and vice versa [CITATION_1] . In other words, by increasing the value of the segmentation parameter, some newer segments may be produced. For very large values of , the number of segments is very high in such a way that for extremely large , the number of extracted segments reach the number of all pixels which are located in the regions of interest. In order to achieve desired results and avoid over-segmentation and under-segmentation problems, the value of the parameter must be properly set. In the present study, this value is manually tuned after extensive sets of experiments. Therefore, we suggest setting this parameter to a fixed value (i.e. for all the lung CT datasets.",
